data.title: Authentic Mexican Restaurant
data.text: This restaurant in mostly frequented by locals. The food and prices are good. I had the fajitas and they were excellent.

data.title: The food and service was excellent.
data.text: The food served in the restaurant is the authentic Mexican food and the Caldo de Res is just fabulous.  Also thee waiters provide dood service.

data.title: Best Hometown place to dine in Mission
data.text: If you are visiting mission and want to eat where the locals ear and experience a true and authentic Tex Mexico menue then this is the place to eat. It's not fancy or spiffy but what it lacks in fluff it makes up for in flavor.  Located in the heart of downtown mission it's an easy drive from anywhere in the vacitity. The menu offers all the traditional plates such as fajitas and enchiladas but you can also experience delicacies like chilaquiles for breakfast or clabaza con Pollo for lunch or dinner. I highly recommend you try and order of re-fried beans as they are hands down spectacular! I promise you will not be dissapointment with the food here which I am sure you will tell all your friends about. I hope you find my review helpful and if so please click below.
